# .privacy-denylist.example — template for privacy_scan.py's denylist.
#
# Copy this file to `.privacy-denylist` (which is git-ignored) and list the
# candidate-specific proper nouns that must never appear in the dossier repo's
# system-layer docs: real name, past/present employers, product/vendor names.
# One term per line. Blank lines and '#' comments are ignored. Matching is
# whole-token and case-insensitive, so "Straiv" flags "STRAIV" but not
# "Straivision".
#
# The real .privacy-denylist stays local and untracked, so the names it holds
# never enter git history — only this placeholder example is committed.

# Real name (as it must not leak into method docs)
# Firstname Lastname

# Employers / clients
# Acme GmbH
# Straiv

# Products / internal codenames
# ProjectFalcon
